<subSubSection pageId="86" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="86.[729,1258,952,1766]" pageId="86">
DIAGNOSIS: Males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BOSSELAERS &amp; JOCQUÉ" authorityYear="2000" box="[1019,1129,1135,1158]" class="Arachnida" family="Corinnidae" genus="Hortipes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baerti">
<emphasis box="[1019,1129,1135,1158]" italics="true" pageId="86">H. baerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are easily recognized by the male palp with a very large RTA provided with four prongs: two short ones at the base in the middle, one directed backward and one directed forward.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="88" pageId="86" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="86.[729,1258,952,1766]" pageId="86">
MALE: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[844,1034,1287,1311]" pageId="86">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length 2.43; carapace 1.22 long, 0.97 wide; length of fe: I 0.97, II 1.05, III 0.81, IV 1.22. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="86">Leg spination.</emphasis>
Fe: I rv 2; IV plt 1 rlt 1; ti: I, II vsp 6; mt: III plt 1 vt 1 rlt 0; IV plt 1 vt 2 rlt 1. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[729,870,1439,1463]" pageId="86">Coloration.</emphasis>
Carapace light olive brown, pal­ er in the cephalic region. Chelicerae, sternum, and legs pale yellow. Abdomen pale yellow, no pattern. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[974,1038,1530,1554]" pageId="86">Palp.</emphasis>
Tibia with large, complex RTA; long frontal prong broad, retrolaterally concave, with denticle in middle of its ventral margin, and distal tip curved outward; posterior prong narrow, retrolaterally concave, curved outward at tip; central prongs near base short, inferior one triangular, superior one slightly more elongate; cym­
